						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in the <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of the Āñjanēyasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>Sadāśiva, 1552 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1474, Paridhāvin, Kārtika śu. 12, Utthānadvādaśi, Saturday</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1552 A.D., October 29, °17.</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged epigraph records gift of money by <hi rend="italic">vipravinōdi</hi> Kēśavayya and another (name lost) to the gods Hanumanta and Rāmēśvara in the <hi rend="italic">agrahāra</hi> of Pinavaḍugūru <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Timmasamudram.</p>						

						</summary>
